   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER TEN THE SPIRIT'S WORK ON AND IN</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>THE BELIEVERS 2 Scripture Reading: John 3:5-6, 8; 1:12-13; 3:6; 1 Pet 1:3; Titus 3:5 OUTLINE Regenerating the convicted and believing believers John 3:5-6, 8: Begetting them to be the children of God John 1:12-13: In their spirit John 3:6.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Through the resurrection of Christ 1 Pet 1:3.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Into the kingdom of God John 3:5.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Washing away the filthiness of the old nature of their old man Titus 3:5: Putting off their old man and putting on the new.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Reconditioning their state from the old creation to the new.</S>
